Mr Sabnani, Mr Uppathil -

It was a pleasure seeing you earlier this afternoon and learning about your
inspiring journey.

Driven by the passion to support future entrepreneurs, I wrote my first
angel check in 2019 to a small company called Adonmo
<http://www.adonmo.com/>, which has since grown to become the market leader
in digital screens in India, valued at more than US$250m.

This investment showed me the power of early startup investment and its
impact: creating not only jobs but also generational wealth.

Following this, I joined my partner Sajid Rahman
<https://www.linkedin.com/in/rahmansajid/> to scale MyAsiaVC
<http://www.myasiavc.com/>, into one of the largest venture syndicates
globally, having invested US$70m+ across more than 260 companies, including
Razorpay, Anthropic, SpaceX, OpenAI, Rupifi, Xendit, Snyk, Big Bang Boom,
Alt Mobility and many others.

Seeing we are at the dawn of the AI & Robotics wave, we are now
building *Contra
VC*, a venture capital fund that invests in cross-border AI & Robotics
innovation right from Hong Kong, which no other fund is currently solving
for.

We are investing in the top 1% technical Asian founders who are building
businesses that will disrupt how businesses operate, money moves,
healthcare innovates and supply chains scale.

I am including herein a deck
<https://www.papermark.com/view/cmkdt9nbe0039kw0470imzas0>, a short video
<https://www.papermark.com/view/cmhx7wm0g0001ld04vcecvaie> and a brief
on venture
capital as an asset class
<https://www.papermark.com/view/cmoh1kqj20006l304movfil8m> for your
preliminary review.

I'm happy to share further details or come to your offices for a detailed
meeting.

We aim to raise $5m for our first close by end June 2026. We are accepting
checks of US$1m from institutions and US$150k from individuals, with larger
checks receiving favourable economics.

We believe this is a once in a lifetime opportunity to invest in technology
that will change the course of humanity and it will be great to have you
alongside us on this journey.

Thank you,
Aabhas

